Excited to share my DevOps project with real-world impact!

I successfully designed and implemented a CI/CD pipeline to automate deployment of a Hotstar-like web application on AWS Cloud.

Tech Stack:
• AWS EC2 (Ubuntu - Free Tier)
• Jenkins (CI/CD Automation)
• Apache Tomcat (Application Server)
• GitHub (Version Control)

Key Achievements:
• Set up Jenkins on EC2 and configured complete CI/CD pipeline
• Automated end-to-end workflow: Checkout → Build → Test → Package → Deploy
• Integrated GitHub with Jenkins for continuous integration
• Deployed application on Tomcat server and made it live via public IP
• Resolved plugin dependency issues and optimized setup

Impact & Metrics:
✔ Reduced manual deployment effort by 90%
✔ Deployment time reduced from ~15 minutes to <2 minutes
✔ Achieved 100% successful automated builds
✔ Enabled real-time monitoring using Jenkins Stage View

Outcome:
Application successfully deployed and accessible on AWS cloud environment.

Key Learning:
Hands-on experience in CI/CD, automation, cloud deployment, and troubleshooting real-world issues.

Special thanks to my trainer KARANAM GURUTEJA sir for valuable guidance and continuous support.

